    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-20T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-20T07:00:00-05:00" n="241"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20/748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kliefoth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-20T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 20, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 20—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Austria’s reaction to German universal military service was one of silent but
                    cordial approval. Austria feels that it too is on the road to military parity by
                    slow stages but with knowledge and consent of former allies whereas Germany
                    secured it secretly and by flagrant violation of treaties. Press here now
                    urgently recommending universal service for Austria which idea finds approval in
                    high official places. Competent Austrian opinion, however, does not envisage war
                    as the outcome of Germany’s declaration and hopefully relies on British
                    statesmanship to calm the situation. Copies mailed to Berlin, Paris, London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kliefoth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
